assed in the course of colonial conquest. Regardless of what the law, media and political discourse dictate, people with personal, ancestral or geographical links to colonialism, or those existing under the weight of its legacy of race and racism, have every right to come to Britain and take back what is theirs.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aEmigration and immigration lawzGreat Britain. 0aImperialismxEconomic aspectsxColonieszGreat Britain. 0aImperialismxEconomic aspectszGreat BritainxColonies. 0aImperialismxEconomic aspectszGreat Britain. 4amanchesterhive variable pricing textbooks. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh  aBorders.  aColonialism.  aEmpire.  aImmigration.  aMigrants.  aPostcolonial.  aasylum seekers.  arefugees.1 aEl-Enany, Nadine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526145437423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526145437/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles